PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1783725539
OL,3,CItalian beaches booked until September
OL,4,Cas tourism weighs on beauty spots
OL,6,FIn February, authorities in Rome
OL,7,Fstarted charging two euros to see the
OL,8,FTrevi Fountain, which was previously
OL,9,Feasily accessible while walking the
OL,10,Fstreets of the capital.
OL,12,FThe Italian government also banned
OL,13,Fcruise ships from entering the
OL,14,Fhistoric centre of Venice in 2021 amid
OL,15,Fconcerns that the famous city was
OL,16,Fbeing destroyed by overtourism.
OL,18,FItaly also has a tourist tax, which
OL,19,Franges from one euro to 10 euros a
OL,20,Fday, depending on the quality of the
OL,21,Faccommodation people stay in.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/7
